snippet.textDisplay:
I still have issues with Sabrina MURDERING--essentially---her twin sister last season! Her sister had better knowledge of magic---and how to use it-- than she did! She also broke a promise that she made to Nick that she would wait for him to return before doing anything.
By killing her sister, she fulfilled the prophecy. And the cruelty--plus dishonesty--that both Sabrina and Ambroise showed towards her twin sister.
There were several posters, from last season, who stated that they had crying jags when Sabrina cold-bloodedly executed her sister. I was so 'off-put' that I am now writing my own 'mandrake' script. I also sent a STRONGLY WORDED email to Archie Comics. I also felt that the twin of Sabrina showed the kind of character traits that have been 'missing' in the 'rea;' Sabrina.
Then there was the issue of the Roz, Harvey and Theo mandrake clones being killed by Theo. More innocent beings being sacrificed in the latar of expediency!..

Had all the 'mandrake friends' survived, they may have been able to show new insights for defeating the Dark Lord.
